verblex: 1. To move your body about in space as a natural consequence of doing something. English = move.
2. To consciously move your body about in space, especially your hips, as you walk. English = sway your hips.
nomlex: 1. The changes in a persons position and the placement of their limbs as they do things or as they go from one place to another, especially by walking. English = movements.
2. The swaying of the hips of a person, especially a woman, as they walk.
